summary: This is a search and seizure warrant issued by the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York authorizing the search of Jeffrey Epstein's residence at 9 East 71st Street in New York City. The warrant seeks evidence related to violations of sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy, listing specific items including a binder labeled 'PB Girls' and massage-related items.

persons.name: Barbara Moses
persons.context: Issued the search and seizure warrant for the premises at 9 East 71st Street, New York, NY.

events.title: Search Warrant Issuance
events.description: A federal search warrant was issued authorizing the search of 9 East 71st Street, New York, NY, for evidence related to sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy.

locations: 9 East 71st Street, New York, New York
keyFacts: The search warrant targets Jeffrey Epstein's New York City residence at 9 East 71st Street for evidence of sex trafficking crimes.
Specific items to be seized include a binder labeled 'PB Girls' and documents regarding victims or potential victims.
Other items listed for seizure include taxidermied dogs, massage tables, busts of female torsos, nude photos in the 'Massage Room', and sex paraphernalia.
The warrant is based on probable cause for violations of Title 18, U.S. Code, Sections 371 (conspiracy) and 1591 (sex trafficking of minors).
The warrant was issued by U.S. Magistrate Judge Barbara Moses and had to be executed by July 7, 2019.
